<br>
If you find a nice undead heavy region, necro wins, period.<br>
<br>
Here's why:<br>
<br>
We get DoTs<br>
We can heal self and damage mob at same time<br>
We can heal others, or pet<br>
We can debuff STR/STA and ATK of mob and give those stats to self / group<br>
Arch Lich regens mana WAY faster than KEI (less downtime)<br>
We have multiple means of attack. <br>
  1. Dot + Pet tank<br>
  2. Fear kite, with or without pet<br>
  3. Root Dot<br>
<br>
It's actually possible for a 56+ necro to come out of a fight with almost as much, or even mana than when he went into a fight.<br>
<br>
In terms of general skillset, we get the abilities of every other class, though perhaps not to the same degree as the specialists, and can literally function as a group of one.<br>
<br>
We get the pets of the Magician class<br>
We get the healing of self and others (cleric/druid/pally)<br>
We get the self HP buffs and skin spells of wizard/cleric<br>
We get Str/Sta/ATK buffs of shaman<br>
We get debuff spells that damage opponent <br>
We get DD spell (720 pt dd), that also heals us<br>
We get Feign Death like monks/SK's<br>
We get slow spell (for use on undead only, but it's still a slow)<br>
We get undead DD spells of the clerics<br>
We can REZ ourselves (93%) <br>
We can summon our corpses (native skill, SK gets lower ver)<br>
We can Gate, and Evac Self (wizard/druid)<br>
We get DoTs that deal massive damage (native skill)<br>
We can MEZ mobs (chanter)<br>
We can Charm undead mobs (chanter)<br>
We can improve mana for others (not like C2. we just send mana to target... )<br>
We can GROUP heal and damage mob at the same time<br>
We can Steal mana from a mob and give it to the group<br>
We can Levitate.. (and our levi gives PR buff, see invis, and water breathing)<br>
We can invis ourselves and invis to undead (eh..even warriors with right gear can invis self)<br>
We even get AE damage spells (wimpy ones, but they're there)<br>
<br>
The only things we CAN'T do are Spirit of Wolf (solved by jboots or run speed3), Group teleport, Summon gear/food, track, and cast damage shields on others. (we get a self damage sheild)<br>
<br>
All in all, the necromancer is the most adaptable, most versatile, most well rounded solo person, indoors or outdoors. It's simply a matter of tactics, and knowing your abilities. Now, in terms of raw speed xp, Nothing competes with a group of AE wizzies on a rampage. However, in the solo arena, I'd be willing to bet I could kill more monters more efficiently in less time than a quad kiting druid, since I can get all my mana and health back in a fraction of the time. Remove KEI from the druid, and I KNOW a necro would be out in front. Add in the Necro epic, and we need even less mana to knock out mobs. To me, it's no contest. Necro is the top. Shaman is a good second, as are Magicians, and then druids, since a druid needs outdoor space to quad kite, and the previous three classes can operate indoors and outdoors. <br>
